  puzzles:
  - id: P001
    title: The Fifth Man
    opening: Five men were walking along a country road when it began to rain. Four
      of them quickened their pace, but the fifth remained unhurried. Eventually,
      all five arrived at the destination together. The four were drenched, but the
      fifth was completely dry.
    answer: The four men were pallbearers carrying a coffin. The fifth man was the
      corpse inside.
    facts:
    - There are five men in total.
    - Four men are walking outside in the rain.
    - One man (the fifth) is not walking by himself.
    - The four men are pallbearers.
    - The pallbearers are carrying a coffin.
    - The fifth man is the corpse inside the coffin.
    - The corpse is dead.
    - The corpse is not moving by his own power.
    - The coffin has a cover or lid.
    - The coffin protects the corpse from getting wet.
    - It is raining during the walk.
    - The four pallbearers are exposed to the rain.
    - The four pallbearers become drenched.
    - The fifth man (corpse) remains completely dry.
    - All five men reach the same destination at the same time.
    - The fifth man does not walk faster or slower; he is carried.
    - The four men quicken their pace because of the rain.
    - "The fifth man\u2019s pace does not change, because he cannot move."
    - "The corpse\u2019s journey ends at the same place as the pallbearers\u2019."
    - The destination is the same for both the living men and the corpse.
    - The fifth man is not alive.
    - The four men are alive.
    - The fifth man does not feel the rain.
    - The fifth man does not carry anything.
    - The fifth man is inside the coffin during the entire journey.
    - The coffin is being carried along the country road.
    - The coffin shields the corpse from the weather.
    - The four pallbearers hold the coffin together.
    - "The corpse\u2019s presence causes there to be five \u201Cmen\u201D total."
    - The rain affects only the men outside the coffin.
    hints:
    - "The fifth person isn\u2019t walking on his own."
    - "\u201CDestination\u201D means something final."
    - The rain affected only the living.
    difficulty: 2
  - id: P002
    title: Indistinguishable Sisters
    opening: "On a rainy day, a man went out dragging a large suitcase. At the door,
      he ran into his wife and happily exchanged a few words with her\u2014then his
      face suddenly twisted in horror. He looked carefully at her side profile, then
      at his watch, and finally glanced at the pouring rain outside. In panic, he
      dragged the suitcase and left the house, never to be seen again."
    answer: "The woman has an identical twin sister. The man was secretly having
      an affair with the sister. During their trysts, the sister drew a mole on her
      cheek to distinguish herself from the wife. Recently, the husband had grown
      tired of his wife and planned to murder her. One rainy day, thinking his wife
      was at work, he invited the sister over. Seeing the woman sitting on the sofa
      without a mole, he panicked\u2014believing his wife had come home early. Fearing
      exposure, he killed her, dismembered the body, and packed it in a suitcase.
      When he left home, he met a woman outside\u2014at first thinking it was his
      lover. After chatting happily for a moment, he noticed she also had no mole.
      Checking the time, he realized it was when his wife usually returned from work.
      Then it dawned on him: the woman he had killed inside was actually his lover\u2014the
      mole had been washed away by the rain. Terrified, he fled and disappeared forever."
    facts: []
    hints:
    - The key lies in the mole.
    - It was raining heavily that day.
    - The wife and her twin look identical.
    difficulty: 4
  - id: P003
    title: Red, Green, and White
    opening: "They looked perfect together, and he seemed happy\u2014but \u201Cgreen
      turned red into white.\u201D A fallen ring, a threatening proof, and the blurred
      remains became his obsession."
    answer: "A senior student had a girlfriend, and they looked perfect together.
      One day he bought a ring to propose (red \u2014 for marriage). On that day,
      a man attacked him, and the ring fell to the ground. Only then did he discover
      the girl was married to that man, an abusive husband. Her coworkers and parents
      all knew the truth but hid it, believing the student gave her hope. She became
      pregnant, and when the husband\u2014a long-distance truck driver\u2014realized
      the timeline didn\u2019t match, he knew he\u2019d been cheated on (green \u2014
      jealousy). The husband later extorted the student, even using the aborted fetus
      as \u201Cproof.\u201D The harassment never stopped, and one day while escaping
      the man, the student was hit by a car and died (white \u2014 funeral)."
    facts: []
    hints:
    - The colors red, green, and white symbolize wedding, jealousy, and death.
    - "The \u201Chusband\u201D being away for long trips is key."
    difficulty: 4
  - id: P004
    title: Waterweed
    opening: A boy walked by the river and chatted with a fisherman. The fisherman
      said something to him, and the boy immediately committed suicide.
    answer: "Years earlier, the boy and his girlfriend played by this river. She
      fell into the water, and he jumped in to save her. The current was strong;
      he managed to grab a handful of \u201Cwaterweed\u201D but failed to pull her
      up. She drowned. Years later, he returned to the same river and chatted with
      a fisherman, who casually said, \u201CThere\u2019s never been any waterweed
      in this river.\u201D The boy realized what he had grabbed that day was her
      hair\u2014and he killed himself in grief."
    facts: []
    hints:
    - "The \u201Cwaterweed\u201D wasn\u2019t waterweed."
    - Something the fisherman said triggered the realization.
    - It happened in the same river years later.
    difficulty: 3
  - id: P005
    title: The Loyal Dog
    opening: "Xiao Qiang owned a very loyal dog. One day he took the dog out for
      a walk\u2014and died."
    answer: 'Xiao Qiang had a heart condition. That day he had a sudden cardiac arrest
      on the street. His loyal dog kept strangers from approaching, barking and guarding
      his owner, so no one dared to help. By the time help arrived, Xiao Qiang was
      dead.

      (Alternate twist: his wife secretly removed his medication to
      claim insurance money.)'
    facts: []
    hints:
    - "The dog didn\u2019t attack him\u2014it tried to protect him."
    - The tragedy was caused by misplaced loyalty.
    difficulty: 2
  - id: P006
    title: "Don\u2019t Save Him!"
    opening: "When we arrived at the house of the food-poisoning victims, everyone
      was too weak to stand, faces pale as paper. Just as we were about to carry
      the most critical elder onto the ambulance, they all cried out in unison: \u201CDon\u2019t
      save him!\u201D"
    answer: The old man had already died earlier. The family had gathered for his
      funeral, but the food they prepared caused mass food poisoning. The paramedics
      thought the old man was another unconscious victim, but the family shouted
      not to waste time on a corpse.
    facts: []
    hints:
    - "The old man wasn\u2019t one of the poisoned victims."
    - The family gathered because of a funeral, not a meal.
    difficulty: 2
  - id: P007
    title: Chocolate
    opening: "Xiao Ming\u2019s little brother kept a pet hamster. One day, the hamster
      died, and the boy was heartbroken. Their mother rewarded him with a piece of
      chocolate the size of the hamster. Some time later, Xiao Ming died. Why?"
    answer: "The little brother wanted a bigger piece of chocolate\u2014so he killed
      his brother to get one the same size as Xiao Ming."
    facts: []
    hints:
    - "The chocolate\u2019s size is always \u201Cthe same as what died.\u201D"
    - "The brother\u2019s logic was literal and cruel."
    difficulty: 3
